    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Romans",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 2,
        "summary": "God will render to every person according to his or her deeds\u2014Both Jews and Gentiles will be judged by gospel laws.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Therefore thou art inexcusable, O man, whosoever thou art that judgest: for wherein thou judgest another, thou condemnest thyself; for thou that judgest doest the same things.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Judgment.",
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But we are sure that the judgment of God is according to truth against them which commit such things.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0know.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Judgment, the Last.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 33
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And thinkest thou this, O man, that judgest them which do such things, and doest the same, that thou shalt escape the judgment of God?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 16:52.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 10:28. TG\u00a0Judgment, the Last.",
                        "start": 118,
                        "end": 126
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Or despisest thou the riches of his goodness and forbearance and longsuffering; not knowing that the goodness of God leadeth thee to repentance?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Treasure.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 4:20 (19\u201320).",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Forbear.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But after thy hardness and impenitent heart treasurest up unto thyself wrath against the day of wrath and revelation of the righteous judgment of God;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0in accordance with.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hardheartedness; Stiffnecked.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Who will render to every man according to his deeds:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0give back, recompense, restore.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Accountability.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 11:6 (5\u20136). TG\u00a0Good Works.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "To them who by patient continuance in well doing seek for glory and honour and immortality, eternal life:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Patience.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 67:13. TG\u00a0Perseverance.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Immortality.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But unto them that are contentious, and do not obey the truth, but obey unrighteousness, indignation and wrath,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Contention.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Disobedience.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Indignation of.",
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 100
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Tribulation and anguish, upon every soul of man that doeth evil, of the Jew first, and also of the Gentile;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 32:10.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sorrow.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0Greek.",
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But glory, honour, and peace, to every man that worketh good, to the Jew first, and also to the Gentile:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Peace of God.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Work, Value of.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0Greek.",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For there is no respect of persons with God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0partiality. Deut. 10:17; Acts 10:34; Rom. 10:12 (12\u201313); Hel. 3:28 (27\u201330). TG\u00a0God, Access to.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 17:35 (35\u201340); 2\u00a0Ne. 26:33 (23\u201333).",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 34
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For as many as have sinned without law shall also perish without law: and as many as have sinned in the law shall be judged by the law;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 12:48. TG\u00a0Accountability; Law of Moses.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 38
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "(For not the hearers of the law are just before God, but the doers of the law shall be justified.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Good Works.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 13:39 (26\u201341).",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For when the Gentiles, which have not the law, do by nature the things contained in the law, these, having not the law, are a law unto themselves:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Which shew the work of the law written in their hearts, their conscience also bearing witness, and their thoughts the mean while accusing or else excusing one another;)",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0Who.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 31:33 (31\u201334); D&C 84:46 (44\u201347).",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 32:5. TG\u00a0Conscience.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 72
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 6:23 (22\u201323).",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 104
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "In the day when God shall judge the secrets of men by Jesus Christ according to my gospel.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 4:5. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Judge.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Gospel.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, thou art called a Jew, and restest in the law, and makest thy boast of God,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And knowest his will, and approvest the things that are more excellent, being instructed out of the law;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And art confident that thou thyself art a guide of the blind, a light of them which are in darkness,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "An instructor of the foolish, a teacher of babes, which hast the form of knowledge and of the truth in the law.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0system, appearance. 2\u00a0Tim. 3:5.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou therefore which teachest another, teachest thou not thyself? thou that preachest a man should not steal, dost thou steal?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hypocrisy.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 9:14 (13\u201314); Alma 39:11 (11\u201312).",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 85
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Stealing.",
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 108
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou that sayest a man should not commit adultery, dost thou commit adultery? thou that abhorrest idols, dost thou commit sacrilege?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Adulterer.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0rob shrines, temples.",
                        "start": 115,
                        "end": 121
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sacrilege.",
                        "start": 122,
                        "end": 131
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1419
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou that makest thy boast of the law, through breaking the law dishonourest thou God?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the name of God is blasphemed among the Gentiles through you, as it is written.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Blaspheme.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 33
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For circumcision verily profiteth, if thou keep the law: but if thou be a breaker of the law, thy circumcision is made uncircumcision.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gal. 5:3. TG\u00a0Circumcision.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore if the uncircumcision keep the righteousness of the law, shall not his uncircumcision be counted for circumcision?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And shall not uncircumcision which is by nature, if it fulfil the law, judge thee, who by the letter and circumcision dost transgress the law?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For he is not a Jew, which is one outwardly; neither is that circumcision, which is outward in the flesh:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But he is a Jew, which is one inwardly; and circumcision is that of the heart, in the spirit, and not in the letter; whose praise is not of men, but of God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 7:51; 2\u00a0Ne. 9:33. TG\u00a0Circumcision.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 7:6.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 64
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 97
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 130,
                        "end": 132
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}